OL,3,CAppeal for victims of sex-offender
OL,4,Cformer Bishop after further reports
OL,5,Cmade
OL,7,FPolice are appealing for victims and
OL,8,Fsurvivors to come forward after the
OL,9,Fconviction of a former Bishop for
OL,10,Fmultiple child sexual offences that
OL,11,Ftook place during the 1980s.
OL,13,FSouth Wales Police confirmed on 7 May
OL,14,Fthat three people have "taken the
OL,15,Ffirst step in coming forward" since 84-
OL,16,Fyear-old Anthony Piece was jailed.
OL,18,FPierce pleaded guilty to five counts
OL,19,Fof indecent assault on a child under
OL,20,Fthe age of 16 at Swansea Crown Court
OL,21,Fin February 2025.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G1/5
